2. ORIGINAL ALGORITHM (SAGCM) & INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY DECLARATION
=======================================================================
This repository introduces and implements the SAGCM (Surface-Adsorbate Grand 
Canonical Modeling) algorithm, a proprietary framework pioneered by the author(s).
The core conceptual and architectural originalities protected herein include:

- The SAGCM framework: An end-to-end Reinforcement Learning solver mapping Operando 
  catalyst evolution through Grand Potential (Ω) optimization.
- The exact hybrid integration schema of Maskable Proximal Policy Optimization 
  (Maskable PPO) decoupled with dual Machine Learning Potentials (e.g., Hybrid Oracle).
- The operando compositional constraint logic, encompassing PID Lagrangian 
  penalties, debt-shaping guidance, and thermodynamic constraint masks.

The SAGCM methodology, the algorithm structure, and all specific heuristic modules 
(`GreedyCOPlacer`, `UMAPotentialShaper`) are original intellectual properties. 
Any academic publications, code implementations, derivative configurations, or 
commercial evaluations utilizing the SAGCM framework or identical design concepts 
must explicitly cite this repository and acknowledge its original inventor(s).

=======================================================================
3. THIRD-PARTY DEPENDENCIES & WEIGHTS ACKNOWLEDGEMENT
=======================================================================
This project utilizes the Universal Materials Accelerator (UMA) foundation 
model developed by FAIR (Meta AI) for energy evaluation operations. 

- The UMA model checkpoints (e.g., `uma-s-1p1.pt`) and associated reference 
  files (`form_elem_refs.yaml`, `iso_atom_elem_refs.yaml`) are NOT the original 
  property of this repository. 
- These weights are loaded via the `fairchem-core` package and are subject to 
  the original FAIR / Open Catalyst Project license agreements (CC-BY-NC 4.0 or MIT as applicable).
- Users of this repository must comply with the official usage restrictions of UMA 
  when deploying the full experimental stack.